                                                                                                                 NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	New Delhi, June 8: Trinamul Congress MP and actor Tapal Pal was today taken to hospital after he suffered a seizure in Parliament.           
	Pal fell unconscious inside the Lok Sabha during a discussion on the motion of thanks to the Presidents address and was initially attended to by doctors inside Parliament.          
	He was then taken to Ram Manohar Lohia hospital in the evening where his condition was stated to be stable. This is the second time in a week that Pal, known to suffer from hypertension, was hospitalised. Doctors will conduct tests on the actor tomorrow. Fellow Trinamul MP Shatabdi Roy accompanied Pal to hospital.                  
	 Toronto (PTI): Canadian authorities have decided to recognise the law degrees of legal professionals from India and other Asian countries as equivalent to those from the UK and Australia. The National Committee on Accreditation, Canada, has decided that three-year, full-time law degrees from common law countries including India, England and Australia should be treated as equivalent.                  
	 Srinagar: An army major, a jawan and three militants have been killed in a two-day encounter, the biggest in Kashmir in the past two months. Major R.V. Ramani Bhai, 29, was killed on Sunday in an ambush in Kupwara, close to the Line of Control. The outfit of the militants is yet to be ascertained.                  
